## Goal

Implement the "library-refresh-and-discover" change for the germinator project. This includes:
- New `library refresh` command to sync metadata from resource files into `library.yaml`
- New `--discover` flag on `library add` to find orphaned resource files

## Instructions

- Follow the PHASE1 implementation workflow from the skill
- Make logical milestone commits (1-5 per iteration)
- Run `mise run check` to verify lint, format, tests pass
- Mark tasks complete in `tasks.md` as you go
- AGENTS.md updates deferred to PHASE3

## Discoveries

- The library.yaml format uses SINGULAR form for resource types (`skill`, `agent`, `command`, `memory`) not plural (`skills`, etc.)
- The `LoadLibrary` function validates resource types using `ResourceType.IsValid()` which expects singular forms
- When a file doesn't exist at the registered path, the refresh implementation searches the directory for a file with matching frontmatter `name` field
- If no file is found with matching name, the resource is skipped silently (left to `validate --fix`)
- The spec says to report name_mismatch error when "frontmatter name doesn't match entry key" - but this only applies when the file EXISTS at the registered path with mismatched name
- If file doesn't exist and we can't find it by searching, we skip silently since we can't distinguish between "deleted" and "renamed to different name"

